# Copilot instructions for Finagler Tailwindâ†’Semantic refactor

Objective:
Convert all Tailwind utility classNames (e.g., p-*, m-*, bg-*, text-*, flex, gap-*, items-*, justify-*, border-*, rounded-*, shadow-*) 
into semantic classNames that correspond to the vocabulary defined in base.css.

Rules:
- Allowed classNames: panel, sidebar, toolbar, button, field, list, text-muted, warning, flex, column, row, center, gap-sm, gap-md, pad-sm, pad-md
- Combine classes logically (e.g. className="panel flex column gap-md")
- Remove all Tailwind-specific utility names
- Preserve existing JSX hierarchy and functional behavior
- Do NOT invent new one-off classes
- Assume every component inherits base.css and domain-specific overrides
